<title>BRAZIL: Brazil's Bovespa index to add four issues.</title>
<headline>Brazil's Bovespa index to add four issues.</headline>
<dateline>SAO PAULO 1997-08-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Sao Paulo bolsa said on Tuesday it will add four shares to the Bovespa index of most-traded stocks, bringing to 51 the number of shares making up its index portfolio.</p>
<p>In a statement, the bourse said preferred shares of utility Eletropaulo, industrial firm Inepar and telecom Telerj and power holding Lightpar's common will be included in the index starting on September 1.</p>
<p>The bolsa issued a breakdown of the new 51-share index, but said the weighting of each share comprising the theoretical Bovespa portfolio for the September-December period will be calculated after the end of August.</p>
<p>((-- James Craig, Sao Paulo newsroom 5511 2485413))</p>
